Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel the @apple{4}. Quarter, core and roughly chop.

Pop the apples in an 18x18cm #oven dish{} with the @salted caramel{120%g} and @sugar{1%tbsp}. Mix well, ensuring the apples are evenly coated. Set aside.

Chop half your @butter{1/2%pack} into 1cm pieces, (you can use the rest later).

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @plain flour{75%g} and the remaining @sugar{74%g}.

Add the chopped butter and rub it in with your fingertips until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Add the @granola{60%g} and mix through.

Top the apples with the crumble mixture, ensuring it's evenly distributed.

Pop the oven dish onto the bottom shelf of the oven.

Bake until the crumble is golden and the caramel sauce is bubbling, ~{30-35%mins}.

Allow to cool slightly before serving.